bib_record.title: Proton elastic scattering from aluminum for 120, 150 and 165 degr. in the energy interval from 2.4 to 5 MeV

free_txt: ITN, Estrada Nacional 10, 2686-953
Sacavem, Portugal
the 6.0 MV Tandem Van de Graaff
accelerator at the Ruder Boskovic Institute in Zagreb.
For the normalization purposes, a 6 nm thick Au layer
was evaporated onto the target.The authors assume that
both cross sections for He-Au and He-Al backscattering
are of pure Rutherford type. The NAu/NAl ratio was
calculated to be 18.9 +- 0.4.
Three surface barrier detectors positioned
at 120, 150 and 165 degr., with a 2.5 msr solid
angle each, were used to detect backscattered
protons from the target.
The following factors were taken into
consideration for estimating the uncertainty:
* the statistical errors of the counting rates of
peak areas for backscattered protons and
* error of determining NAu/NAl ratio.
Errors of the detector angular settings were estimated
to be negligible.
Uncertainties due to dead time, solid angle and
improper charge measurement are eliminated with the
normalization to backscattering protons from
gold.
* EN-RSL The energy calibration of the accelerator was
made using the  27Al(p,gamma) resonance at 991.9 keV
and the 7Li(p,n) reaction  threshold at 1880.4 keV.
